==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
*Probably from the base of [[κολυμβάω]] {{GG|2865}}; orderly arrangement, that is, decoration; by implication the world (in a wide or narrow sense, including its inhabitants, literally or figuratively [morally]):

===Pronunciation===
*[[κόσμος]] / kosmos / kos'-mos

===Noun===
'''Κόσμος'''

# adorning, [[world]].

